text: Okay I've had just had enough of this I've been a fan of the Angry Birds franchise for quite a long time ever since I was 3 (I'm 12 now) I  downloaded every single game they released bought all of their merchandise I made videos about it I I was that much of a fan. I loved everything Rovio put out for Angry Birds that is until  Angry Birds Transformers and Epic came out I was a little bit off put by it and it wasn't exactly my favorite one but I was still okay with it then the Angry Birds movie came out I was ecstatic to see it in the theaters and I thought it was great when watched. That was when I was maybe 9 and I still thought the franchise could do no wrong. But the realization soon came to me that... Angry Birds as a whole was going down hill. I rewatched the movie and didn't like it, the new games were lame candy crush ripoffs, and Nobody as a whole really cared anymore, this sequel makes me feel.....crushed in what Rovio has done to what I consider my "childhood" ( yes I know that sounds stupid I just didn't know how to say it) I do understand that all good things come to an end but it's just sad to me that Rovio can't accept the fact that their franchise had their chance in popularity and they continue to look as if everyone cares about they franchise. This may sound really stupid to a lot of people and I'm fine with that because the Internet doesn't allow opinions. But I just want to say...... bye Rovio thanks for the great times.
